title: Tale of Gallus
author: BattlingAcorn45
pages:
#-     
        The tale
            of 
  Gallus the Gladiator
#- Once Upon a Time there was a gladiator, this gladiator went by the name of Gallus. Gallus was born and raised in the nation of S.P.Q.R.! Gallus lived a happy life in this amazing nation (that you should really think about joining if you love romans or just want to be in a good community) until 
#- one day Gallus was sent off to fight in the Colosseum!

The Colosseum was a place of terror, fun and everything in between. Gallus was a weak man, he had done nothing but farm his whole life, but he still had to fight in the Colosseum. There were no excuses!
#- Finally, the day had come, Gallus said his goodbyes to everyone he loved, with no hope of returning home that night. As soon as Gallus arrived at the Colosseum  he was filled with nerves, yet at the bottom of his nervousness was a tiny bit of excitement.

3. 2. 1. Fight! The fight 
#- had begun; there were ten men of all shapes and sizes fighting in the Colosseum. Except one of these men wasn't fighting. It was Gallus! Gallus had decided to hide behind one of the pillars spead around the outside of the arena. He watched as one man he had seen before took, took 
#- down every single man; this man was always the strongest, the fastest, the biggest. Everyone feared him. His name wa Brutus. Brutus had bullied Gallus his whole life, it was tine for Gallus to take revenge! 

Although the underdog, Gallus 
#- bravely stepped up to fight Brutus. Brutus had a club in his right hand and a shield in his left, yet all Gallus could find was a pebble beside his right foot. Gallus had one chance. Now was his time. He picked up this pebble, drew back his arm, lunged forward and released! The whole crowd 
#- watched in awe as the pebble flew through the air like a bullet. Flying, flying, Thud! It had hit him, Gallus just hit Brutus. The crowd erupted thinking the underdog had won. This was quickly silenced by the fact that Brutus just continued walking towards Gallus. After all that excitement and
#- for a split second even a thought that Gallus had won, it was looking like it would end as expected, Brutus being the only one to survive. It wasn't over yet though. 

gallus looked to his left then his right, there were no weapons anywhere, 
#- surely he was done for. "Gallus, Gallus" someone screamed. Confused, Gallus turned to look at the person screaming. It was on of the senators, the great people in charge of the nation. At that moment Gallus realised that the senator had hurled an item towards Gallus, unable 
#- to make out what it was, Gallus stuck out a hand ready to catch it. All while Brutus was only two metres away, still approaching slowly. 

It was only when Gallus had caught it, he realised it was a small yet sharp dagger. Knowing he only had one chance,
#- Gallus started sprinting towards Brutus. Running faster than he ever had before. As Gallus approached Brutus he started to slife, right under Brutus' legs. Brutus wasn't quick enough to react thanks to all the gear he had on. While sliding Gallus stuck the knife up, slicing Brutus 
#- clean in half. It was over. Gallus had done it. The crowd erupted, children with their parents, Grandparents cheering with their children. But who was cheering the loudest? The senators! It had been done. He would return home that night. Gallus was victorious. The 
#- underdog had achieved the impossible!



Thank you for reading the book. If you want to read more books come back to the shop in S.P.Q.R!
#- 